{
  "texts": [
    "Finally, this approach does not rely on specific feature extraction techniques but rather automatically learns the most relevant features through the network.Li et al. [511] proposed DEEPRL4FL, a fault localization approach for buggy statements/methods.",
    "DEEPRL4FL exploits the image classification and pattern recognition capability of the CNN to apply to the code coverage matrix.",
    "CNNs are capable of learning the relationships among nearby cells via a small filter and can recognize the visual characteristic features to discriminate faulty and non-faulty statements/methods.",
    "To date, DEEPRL4FL still holds the best performance in terms of the Top-1 metric.Lou et al. [512] proposed GRACE, a method-level FL approach based on the GNN.",
    "GRACE represents a program by a graph, where nodes represent code elements or tests, and edges represent coverage relationships or code structures."
  ]
}